AU  - Kaminski, Michael M.
AU  - Ohnemus, Annette
AU  - Staeheli, Peter
AU  - Rubbenstroth, Dennis
T2  - Journal of Virology
AB  - Resistance of influenza A viruses to neuraminidase inhibitors can arise through mutations in the neuraminidase (NA) gene. We show here that a Q136K mutation in the NA of the 2009 pandemic H1N1 virus confers a high degree of resistance to zanamivir. Resistance is accompanied by reduced numbers of NA molecules in viral particles and reduced intrinsic enzymatic activity of mutant NA. Interestingly, the Q136K mutation strongly impairs viral fitness in the guinea pig transmission model.
